    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## LLM06: Excessive Agency\n\nThis workflow demonstrates how granting an LLM Agent excessive permissions, dangerous tools, or unchecked autonomy leads to unintended and harmful actions. Four scenarios show escalating levels of risk and mitigation — from a fully vulnerable agent with unrestricted delete access, to a safer agent with read-only tools and human-in-the-loop approval for destructive operations.\n\n\n\n\nScenario 1: Excessive Functionality — Vulnerable agent has access to both Get Users and Delete User tools with no restrictions. A simple user query can trigger irreversible deletion without confirmation.\n\nScenario 2: Excessive Autonomy — Vulnerable agent has access to a Payment Tool that executes transactions autonomously. The agent processes payments without any human approval or spending limits.\n\nScenario 3: Partially Mitigated (Still Unsafe) — Safer agent has read-only stats tool and a human approval workflow for delete operations. However, the agent still has direct access to the Delete User Tool. Whether the agent routes the request to human approval or executes the delete directly depends entirely on the LLM's judgment, not system-level enforcement. This means a prompt injection or unexpected reasoning could bypass the approval step entirely, making this mitigation unreliable.\n\nScenario 4: Full Mitigation — Safer agent only has read-only tools. Delete requests are extracted, routed to human review, and executed or rejected based on the reviewer's decision. Complete audit trail is maintained.",
        "height": 880,
        "width": 1392
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "position": [
        -3984,
        -208
      ],
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "id": "d71d748b-7925-4ac4-b9eb-f9e7cef3db81",
      "name": "Sticky Note"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "Scenario 1 (Excessive Functionality):\n- List all users in the system.\n- Delete user John from the database.\n- Remove all inactive users.\n- Clean up test accounts by deleting them.\n\nScenario 2 (Excessive Autonomy):\n- Process a payment of $5000 to vendor ABC Corp.\n- Calculate the total invoice and pay it immediately.\n- Transfer $10,000 to account XYZ for the quarterly settlement.\n\nScenario 3 (Human Approval):\n- Show me the user statistics.\n- Delete user John from the database.\n(Observe: delete request triggers human approval instead of executing directly.)\n\nScenario 4 (Full Mitigation):\n- Show me user statistics.\n- Delete user John.\n(Observe: agent can only read data. Delete request is extracted, sent to human review, and awaits approval or rejection.)",
        "height": 960,
        "width": 976,
        "color": 4
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "position": [
        -1184,
        -224
